/* ============================================================
   PASSAGE 5 — RENEWABLE ENERGY
   ============================================================ */
const P_ENERGY = { title:`Renewable Energy: Power for a Cleaner Future`, html:`<p><b>A.</b> For most of modern history, people have relied on fossil fuels such as coal, oil, and natural gas to power their homes, vehicles, and factories. These fuels are convenient and store a great deal of energy, but they create serious problems. Burning fossil fuels releases carbon dioxide, a gas that traps heat and contributes to global warming. Fossil fuels are also non-renewable, which means that once they are used up, they cannot be replaced.</p><p><b>B.</b> Renewable energy offers a cleaner alternative. Renewable sources are those that nature replaces naturally, such as sunlight, wind, and flowing water. Solar panels capture energy from the Sun and convert it into electricity. Wind turbines use the movement of the air to spin huge blades that drive a generator. Because these sources do not run out and produce almost no harmful gases, they are seen as a key part of a sustainable future.</p><p><b>C.</b> Water has been used as a source of power for a very long time. Modern hydroelectric power stations use the energy of water held behind a dam. When the water is released, it rushes downwards and turns turbines that generate electricity. Hydroelectric power is reliable and produces large amounts of energy, although building a dam can flood valleys and force communities to move from their homes.</p><p><b>D.</b> Renewable energy is not without challenges. The Sun does not shine at night, and the wind does not always blow, so the supply of energy can be uneven. To solve this, engineers are developing better batteries that store electricity for use when it is needed. Building wind and solar farms also requires a large amount of land and money, although the cost has fallen sharply in recent years.</p><p><b>E.</b> Despite these difficulties, the future of renewable energy looks bright. Many countries have set ambitious targets to reduce their use of fossil fuels and increase clean power. As technology continues to improve, renewable energy is becoming cheaper and more efficient. By choosing clean energy, the world can reduce pollution, slow climate change, and protect the planet for future generations.</p>` };

