/* ============================================================
   PASSAGE 7 — ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE
   ============================================================ */
const P_AI = { title:`Artificial Intelligence in Everyday Life`, html:`<p><b>A.</b> Artificial intelligence, often shortened to AI, is the use of computer systems to perform tasks that normally need human thinking. These tasks include recognising faces, understanding speech, translating languages, and making decisions. Although AI may sound like something from a science-fiction film, it has quietly become part of daily life for millions of people, often without them even noticing.</p><p><b>B.</b> Many of the tools that people use every day already contain AI. When a phone unlocks by recognising its owner's face, AI is at work. When a streaming service suggests a film that a viewer might enjoy, it is using AI to study that person's past choices. Voice assistants that answer spoken questions, and maps that find the fastest route through traffic, all rely on the same kind of technology.</p><p><b>C.</b> Most modern AI works through a process called machine learning. Instead of being given a fixed set of rules, the computer is shown a huge number of examples and slowly learns to find patterns within them. For instance, a program can be shown thousands of pictures of cats until it learns to identify a cat in a new image it has never seen before. The more examples the system studies, the better it usually becomes.</p><p><b>D.</b> AI brings many benefits to society. In hospitals, it can help doctors find diseases in medical scans earlier and more accurately. In science, it can analyse enormous amounts of data far faster than any human could. AI can also take over boring or dangerous jobs, freeing people to focus on more creative and rewarding work. In these ways, the technology has the power to improve many lives.</p><p><b>E.</b> However, the rise of AI also raises serious concerns. Some people worry that machines could replace human workers and cause unemployment. There are also questions about privacy, because AI systems often collect large amounts of personal information. Many experts argue that AI must be developed carefully and fairly, with sensible rules, so that its benefits are shared widely and its risks are kept under control.</p>` };

